# VOXERA 2026 — Production Deployment Guide
> Optimized for: **Fastest loads** · **Zero networking issues** · **No server crashes**

---

## Architecture

```
Users ──→ Vercel (Frontend CDN) ──→ Railway (Backend API) ──→ Neon (PostgreSQL)
              Edge-cached                Auto-restart            Serverless DB
              Global CDN                 Health checks           Connection pooling
              ~50ms loads                Zero downtime           Auto-scaling
```

| Layer | Platform | Why |
|-------|----------|-----|
| **Frontend** | **Vercel** (Free) | Edge CDN with 100+ global PoPs, India nodes in Mumbai & Hyderabad. Static files served in ~50ms. Zero cold starts. |
| **Backend** | **Railway** ($5/mo Pro) | Always-on container, auto-restarts on crash, health monitoring, 99.9% uptime SLA. |
| **Database** | **Neon** (Free) | Already set up. Serverless PostgreSQL, auto-scales, connection pooling built-in. |

---

## Step 1: Prepare the Project

### 1a. Create [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/chara/Downloads/vzzz13/vercel.json) for API proxy

Create this file in your project root so Vercel proxies all `/api/*` calls to your Railway backend:

```json
{
  "rewrites": [
    { "source": "/api/:path*", "destination": "https://YOUR_RAILWAY_URL.railway.app/api/:path*" },
    { "source": "/uploads/:path*", "destination": "https://YOUR_RAILWAY_URL.railway.app/uploads/:path*" }
  ]
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Replace `YOUR_RAILWAY_URL` with your actual Railway domain after Step 3.

### 1b. Push to GitHub
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "VOXERA 2026 - production ready"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/voxera-2026.git
git push -u origin main
```

---

## Step 2: Deploy Frontend on Vercel

1. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) → **Sign in with GitHub**
2. Click **"Add New Project"** → Import your `voxera-2026` repo
3. Configure:
   - **Framework Preset**: `Vite`
   - **Build Command**: `npm install --legacy-peer-deps && npm run build`
   - **Output Directory**: `dist`
   - **Install Command**: `npm install --legacy-peer-deps`
4. Add **Environment Variable**:
   - `VITE_API_URL` = `https://YOUR_RAILWAY_URL.railway.app` (update after Step 3)
5. Click **Deploy**

### Add Custom Domain on Vercel
1. Go to **Project Settings** → **Domains**
2. Add `voxera2026.in`
3. At your domain registrar, add:
   - **A record**: `76.76.21.21`
   - **CNAME** for `www`: `cname.vercel-dns.com`

---

## Step 3: Deploy Backend on Railway

1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app) → **Sign in with GitHub**
2. Click **"New Project"** → **"Deploy from GitHub Repo"**
3. Select your `voxera-2026` repo

### Configure Build & Start
In Railway → **Settings** tab:
- **Build Command**: `npm install --legacy-peer-deps`
- **Start Command**: `npm run server`

### Environment Variables
In Railway → **Variables** tab, add ALL of these:

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | `postgresql://...` (your Neon connection string) |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Random 64+ character string ([generate here](https://generate-secret.vercel.app/64)) |
| `ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH` | Your bcrypt hash from [.env](file:///c:/Users/chara/Downloads/vzzz13/.env) |
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | Your Resend key |
| `RAZORPAY_KEY_ID` | Your Razorpay key |
| `RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET` | Your Razorpay secret |
| `FRONTEND_URL` | `https://voxera2026.in,https://www.voxera2026.in` |
| `PORT` | `3000` |
| `NODE_ENV` | `production` |

### Get Your Railway URL
After deploy, go to **Settings** → **Networking** → **Generate Domain**.
Copy the URL (e.g., `voxera-api-production.up.railway.app`).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Now go back to **Vercel** and update [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/chara/Downloads/vzzz13/vercel.json) with this Railway URL, then redeploy.

### Enable Health Checks
Railway → **Settings** → **Health Check Path**: `/api/events`
This ensures Railway auto-restarts your server if it becomes unresponsive.

---

## Step 4: Update Vercel Proxy URL

After getting your Railway URL, update [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/chara/Downloads/vzzz13/vercel.json):

```json
{
  "rewrites": [
    { "source": "/api/:path*", "destination": "https://voxera-api-production.up.railway.app/api/:path*" },
    { "source": "/uploads/:path*", "destination": "https://voxera-api-production.up.railway.app/uploads/:path*" }
  ]
}
```

Commit and push — Vercel auto-redeploys.

---

## Why This Setup Is Best

### ⚡ Fastest Loads
- Static HTML/CSS/JS served from **Vercel's edge CDN** (India PoPs in Mumbai/Hyderabad)
- Users get the page in **~50ms** instead of waiting for a server to respond
- Images, fonts, scripts all cached at the edge
- Gzip/Brotli compression automatic

### 🔒 Zero Networking Issues
- Frontend and API are **separate services** — if one goes down, the other stays up
- Vercel handles SSL, DNS, and CDN automatically
- CORS is configured to accept both `voxera2026.in` and `www.voxera2026.in`
- Rate limiting prevents abuse (auth: 10/15min, contact: 5/15min)

### 💪 No Server Crashes
- Railway **auto-restarts** your Express server if it crashes
- Health check endpoint ensures Railway detects unresponsive servers
- Connection pool set to 20 — handles traffic spikes
- Neon serverless DB auto-scales — no connection limits
- `compression` + `helmet` middleware already configured

